WEBVTT

00:01.836 --> 00:03.379
[ Speaking Japanese ]

00:03.421 --> 00:12.179
♪♪

00:12.221 --> 00:20.980
♪♪

00:21.021 --> 00:32.074
♪♪

00:32.116 --> 00:33.868
Would somebody please tell me
what the [bleep]

00:33.909 --> 00:35.578
these Japanese cowboys
is all about?

00:36.996 --> 00:39.498
♪♪

00:39.540 --> 00:41.208
Nate: I told you the town
was this way.

00:41.250 --> 00:42.460
I looks like
a ghost town.

00:42.501 --> 00:44.462
No, I saw people
from the plane.

00:44.503 --> 00:47.006
-It's really creepy.
-Yeah, well, it's shelter,

00:47.047 --> 00:49.592
so just stop being
so negative, please.

00:49.633 --> 00:51.761
Sorry. My first plane
crash and drug trip

00:51.802 --> 00:53.721
must be affecting
my positivity somehow.

00:53.763 --> 00:54.764
You know what, man...

00:56.807 --> 01:00.728
Hello?!
Anybody here?!

01:00.770 --> 01:03.981
Hello! Anyone?

01:04.023 --> 01:06.984
Hello! We need help!

01:08.986 --> 01:10.279
Hello!

01:11.781 --> 01:13.908
-Oh! Hey! Hey!
-Oh! Hey!

01:13.949 --> 01:16.577
-Hi! We're so lost!
-Hi, how are you?

01:16.619 --> 01:19.455
Thank God. Oh, my God.

01:19.497 --> 01:21.165
-Oh!
-Whoa, whoa! Gun down!

01:21.207 --> 01:23.000
-Please!
-Reach for the sky.

01:23.042 --> 01:24.418
We'll reach, okay, okay!

01:24.460 --> 01:26.545
Please, please,
we mean you no harm!

01:26.587 --> 01:27.880
Robin: We were just --
we were in a plane crash,

01:27.922 --> 01:29.590
and we're super lost.
We just need help.

01:29.632 --> 01:31.467
Please, man! We got children.
Don't do this!

01:31.509 --> 01:32.802
Stop right there.

01:32.843 --> 01:34.261
We're stopped, we're not
walking any further.

01:34.303 --> 01:35.763
Yeah, please just
put the gun down!

01:35.805 --> 01:38.349
This town ain't big enough
for the two of us.

01:38.390 --> 01:41.310
Can he see us?

01:41.352 --> 01:42.770
Put the gun down,
we will walk

01:42.812 --> 01:44.355
right out
of this town right now.

01:44.396 --> 01:46.649
There's a snake in my boot.

01:46.690 --> 01:48.234
What?
What?

01:48.275 --> 01:49.902
I told you there were
snakes out here.

01:49.944 --> 01:51.695
Shh!
Hold on. Guys, something's
not right about this.

01:51.737 --> 01:53.280
Does this guy have "Andy"
written on the bottom

01:53.322 --> 01:54.615
of his boot?
Stop talking.

01:54.657 --> 01:56.283
To infinity...

01:56.325 --> 01:59.119
What?
...and beyond!

01:59.161 --> 02:01.997
Go ahead...
Whoa, whoa!

02:02.039 --> 02:04.667
-...make my day.
-That's not even from a Western.

02:04.708 --> 02:09.004
Whoa. Oh, whoa, whoa.
Whoa, whoa! Everybody guns down!

02:09.046 --> 02:10.881
Please! We are just a family!

02:10.923 --> 02:12.341
We mean you no harm.

02:12.383 --> 02:15.094
[ Speaking Japanese ]

02:17.805 --> 02:20.224
[ Scoffs, laughs ]

02:20.266 --> 02:21.559
Reach for the sky!

02:21.600 --> 02:23.185
Okay, we're reached,
we're reached!

02:23.227 --> 02:27.982
♪♪

02:28.023 --> 02:29.692
Okay.

02:29.733 --> 02:32.027
On my mark, you run over there,
protect the children.

02:32.069 --> 02:33.988
Wh-What are you gonna do?
What I always do.

02:34.029 --> 02:35.364
Oh, God,
don't say "get some."

02:35.406 --> 02:36.782
Please don't get some.
Please don't get some.

02:36.824 --> 02:38.367
Please don't get some.
Please don't get some!

02:38.409 --> 02:39.952
Get some! Go!

02:39.994 --> 02:47.877
♪♪

02:47.918 --> 02:49.879
[ Screams ]

02:49.920 --> 02:52.172
Oh, my God!
I just killed somebody!

02:52.214 --> 02:53.549
Great! Kill more!

02:54.592 --> 02:56.677
Ugh!

02:56.719 --> 02:58.387
Oh! [ Grunts ]

02:59.763 --> 03:02.474
Reach for the sk--

03:02.516 --> 03:04.852
[ Chuckling ]

03:05.769 --> 03:07.521
Delilah, no!

03:07.563 --> 03:11.734
♪♪

03:11.775 --> 03:13.110
What is happening?!

03:16.238 --> 03:19.950
[ Speaking Japanese ]

03:19.992 --> 03:21.243
[ Laughs ]

03:21.285 --> 03:23.412
Go big or go home.

03:23.454 --> 03:25.539
[ Speaking Japanese ]

03:28.417 --> 03:30.210
They're dying,
but they're not bleeding.

03:30.252 --> 03:31.462
What are they?

03:31.503 --> 03:33.839
Zombies.
Cosplayers.

03:33.881 --> 03:36.342
[ Gunshots, shouting ]
Babe.

03:36.383 --> 03:38.719
Babe, get out of the road!
You're gonna get shot!

03:38.761 --> 03:41.347
-Sweetheart, they're blanks.
-What?!

03:41.388 --> 03:44.058
It's a bunch of Pacific Rim
LARPers playing dress-up.

03:44.099 --> 03:45.851
What are you talking about?
LARPers.

03:45.893 --> 03:47.144
I don't know
what that means?!

03:47.186 --> 03:48.395
Live action role-playing.

03:48.437 --> 03:51.023
Oh, you think
this is role-playing?!

03:51.065 --> 03:52.733
I don't think so, sister!

03:52.775 --> 03:55.611
[ Groaning ]

03:55.653 --> 03:57.237
See?

03:57.279 --> 03:59.239
[ Speaks Japanese ]

03:59.281 --> 04:01.116
Oh, shit.

04:01.158 --> 04:03.911
[ All groaning ]

04:03.953 --> 04:06.914
I guess I killed that guy
like 10 times.

04:06.956 --> 04:09.750
♪ Somewhere behind
the mountains ♪

04:09.792 --> 04:13.128
♪ There is a place
I'm thinkin' ♪

04:13.170 --> 04:15.798
[ Distorted music plays ]

04:18.133 --> 04:20.010
Hey, Delilah,
shoot me with the gun.

04:20.052 --> 04:21.845
[ Gunshot ]

04:21.887 --> 04:24.139
Ah -- Ah -- Aah!

04:24.181 --> 04:26.976
This is the best
vacation ever!

04:27.017 --> 04:32.064
♪♪

04:32.106 --> 04:33.732
[ Laughs ]

04:33.774 --> 04:37.569
[ Speaking Japanese ]

04:37.611 --> 04:39.238
So what is this place?

04:39.279 --> 04:42.282
Well, for about three years now,
Mr. Tanaka and his associates

04:42.324 --> 04:44.410
have been coming up here
for a few weeks out of the year

04:44.451 --> 04:46.578
to live out their
favorite cowboy movies.

04:46.620 --> 04:48.122
Isn't that something?

04:48.163 --> 04:49.999
It's -- It's kind of awesome.
I got to admit.

04:50.040 --> 04:53.711
You know, all the guns
and the dresses, they're just...

04:53.752 --> 04:56.255
Everything looks and feels
so real.

04:56.296 --> 04:57.840
Oh, thank you.

04:57.881 --> 05:00.384
I mean, we take a lot of pride
in being period correct.

05:00.426 --> 05:03.470
Without the danger, of course.
It's all just make believe.

05:03.512 --> 05:05.723
Oh, okay, so you're not
actually a prostitute.

05:05.764 --> 05:07.433
Babe!
I'm just saying,

05:07.474 --> 05:09.476
she's not actually available
for sexual services,

05:09.518 --> 05:11.145
so stop looking at her
like she is.

05:11.186 --> 05:12.855
I'm not.

05:12.896 --> 05:15.149
Listen, we need to get out
of here. How do we do that?

05:15.190 --> 05:17.151
Uh, well,
we have a shuttle

05:17.192 --> 05:18.569
leaving for Fairbanks
in two days.

05:18.610 --> 05:20.320
I mean, you
and your family are --

05:20.362 --> 05:22.281
No, no, no, no, that's --
that's not soon enough.

05:22.322 --> 05:23.782
Do you have a radio?
Babe!

05:23.824 --> 05:25.492
What?
Cool down, she's being nice.

05:25.534 --> 05:27.453
She needs to put on
a sweater.

05:27.494 --> 05:28.829
She does not.

05:28.871 --> 05:32.332
Do not let her ruin
your authenticity.

05:32.374 --> 05:34.126
Thank you.
You're welcome.

05:34.168 --> 05:37.671
Um, Mr. Tanaka has offered up
his cabin. It's up on the hill.

05:37.713 --> 05:41.091
And there are clothes,
and you can take a bath...

05:41.133 --> 05:42.843
which it looks like
you sorely need.

05:42.885 --> 05:44.845
She does. And thank you
again for everything.

05:44.887 --> 05:48.599
For all of it. Like,
just thank you so, so much.

05:48.640 --> 05:51.143
Aw. Well,
I would politely ask

05:51.185 --> 05:53.020
that you stay out of
the town center.

05:53.062 --> 05:56.523
Because we have crafted another
high noon duel at 3:00 P.M.

05:56.565 --> 05:58.025
The boys are gonna
fight the Pinkertons.

05:58.067 --> 05:59.860
Come to collect
for the banks.

05:59.902 --> 06:01.320
[ Both laugh ]

06:01.361 --> 06:03.113
Fun fact about
the Pinkertons --

06:03.155 --> 06:05.074
Oh, do we look like we give
a shit about American history?

06:05.115 --> 06:07.284
We're not Japanese.
Come on, let's go.

06:07.326 --> 06:13.916
♪♪

06:13.957 --> 06:16.752
We should really talk
about what we're gonna do.

06:16.794 --> 06:19.296
We did already. We're gonna
turn ourselves in. Right?

06:19.338 --> 06:20.756
I'm gonna pretend
I don't know anything

06:20.798 --> 06:22.299
and act like
I'm a big, dumb idiot

06:22.341 --> 06:23.884
that doesn't know
how things work.

06:26.845 --> 06:28.555
He's really good
with a gun, huh?

06:28.597 --> 06:30.682
Nice shooting, boy!
I know about all that.

06:30.724 --> 06:32.559
But once we're past
all the legal shit,

06:32.601 --> 06:34.561
you know, we just put
these kids through so much.

06:34.603 --> 06:36.355
They don't deserve
this life.

06:36.396 --> 06:39.316
I mean, I'm doing the same thing
to them that my dad did to me.

06:39.358 --> 06:42.111
I'm gonna wake up one day,
and they're just gonna be gone.

06:42.152 --> 06:45.864
Mnh-mnh. No way, man.
This family is due for a win.

06:45.906 --> 06:47.866
This family doesn't get wins.
We don't even get ties.

06:49.576 --> 06:51.912
At least when I was being
developmentally neglected,

06:51.954 --> 06:53.997
we stayed in fancy
French hotels.

06:54.039 --> 06:57.584
This, we're just,
you know, on the run in...

06:57.626 --> 06:59.169
Like, wow, that's smooth.

06:59.211 --> 07:01.046
Right?
Yeah.

07:01.088 --> 07:02.631
Yeah, and these are
my babies, you know?

07:02.673 --> 07:04.675
Mm-hmm.
And I'm --
I'm forcing them.

07:04.716 --> 07:07.052
I'm forcing them to...

07:07.094 --> 07:08.637
Is it made of butter?

07:08.679 --> 07:10.222
It's really...
It's so good.

07:10.264 --> 07:11.807
...really, really good.

07:11.849 --> 07:14.101
I'll take this over a fancy,
snooty French hotel any day.

07:14.143 --> 07:15.686
It's like
a firm handshake.

07:15.727 --> 07:18.730
Mm.
Like a successful merger.

07:18.772 --> 07:20.274
Mm.

07:20.315 --> 07:22.776
Get some.

07:22.818 --> 07:24.528
I guess
we could do worse.

07:24.570 --> 07:26.780
We could do way worse.
Yeah. Hey, kids?

07:26.822 --> 07:30.868
Kids?! Don't go away. Come back.
Mommy needs a hug.

07:30.909 --> 07:33.620
Yeah, it's probably best you
don't kiss them and hug them

07:33.662 --> 07:35.706
while you're naked
and drunk in a hot tub.

07:35.747 --> 07:37.291
I'm not drunk yet.

07:37.332 --> 07:39.918
Right, well...
you will be.

07:39.960 --> 07:41.628
You will be.

07:43.463 --> 07:45.632
Okay, so, Bill, you're gonna
jump out of the barrel.

07:45.674 --> 07:47.301
And you better have worked
up that Irish accent.

07:47.342 --> 07:49.344
Oh, we've been doing this show
for three years now.

07:49.386 --> 07:51.930
We haven't got anything better
than the barrel surprise?

07:51.972 --> 07:54.474
Do you have a better dramatic
entrance planned for us, Bill?!

07:54.516 --> 07:55.976
'Cause I'd love
to see that!

07:56.018 --> 07:59.188
[ Trumpet plays "Dixie"
over loudspeaker ]

08:01.315 --> 08:03.483
Can that be any more
anachronistic, Bill?

08:07.362 --> 08:11.783
♪♪

08:11.825 --> 08:14.870
Oh, God.
Jesus Christ.

08:14.912 --> 08:17.748
This is a goddamn ghost town!
No, they're here.

08:17.789 --> 08:20.167
No, there is
literally no one here.

08:20.209 --> 08:22.502
Hey, hey, Robin Randall!
Robin Randall, are you here?

08:22.544 --> 08:24.296
Robin Randall!
Oh, my God!

08:24.338 --> 08:26.423
This is the Alaskan
Free State Battalion,

08:26.465 --> 08:29.635
1st Mountain Division.
I'm General Mark.

08:29.676 --> 08:32.429
Joining me is
Driver General Kevin

08:32.471 --> 08:35.307
and Maps General Carol.

08:35.349 --> 08:39.436
Surrender peacefully
and we'll spare your lives.

08:39.478 --> 08:42.105
I hate you so much.

08:44.107 --> 08:47.569
So what if we did live in this
magic whiskey old West-ville?

08:47.611 --> 08:49.821
What would we do?

08:49.863 --> 08:51.949
Well, probably start every day
with one of these --

08:51.990 --> 08:55.369
oh! -- amazing sex baths.

08:55.410 --> 08:58.247
And then, I don't know,
split wood.

08:58.288 --> 09:00.832
What would I do?
You'd be splitting wood.

09:00.874 --> 09:04.002
I'll be inside, showering off
all the dirt from the sex bath.

09:04.044 --> 09:05.462
Oh, you know,
we could make candles.

09:05.504 --> 09:07.256
That sounds like
something people

09:07.297 --> 09:09.216
who lost their shit
would do, right?
Yeah, I guess so.

09:09.258 --> 09:10.676
How do you even make candles?
What are you talking about?

09:10.717 --> 09:12.261
You melt other candles
and make them out of those?

09:12.302 --> 09:13.512
Where do you get
those candles?

09:13.553 --> 09:14.930
Other candles.
But then where do you --

09:14.972 --> 09:17.349
-Let's go.
-No, get out, get out!!

09:17.391 --> 09:18.809
Out? I'm already outside.

09:18.850 --> 09:20.394
We have to run!
The heat's here!

09:20.435 --> 09:21.937
I told you this family
doesn't get wins.

09:21.979 --> 09:23.438
No, we're not running.

09:23.480 --> 09:25.107
I'm not giving you guys
the life my dad gave me.

09:25.148 --> 09:26.984
We're stopping right now.

09:29.945 --> 09:31.405
Are you guys
still having sex?

09:31.446 --> 09:32.906
No!

09:32.948 --> 09:34.908
Yes.

09:38.161 --> 09:47.587
♪♪

09:47.629 --> 09:50.674
Ma'am, is that them?

09:50.716 --> 09:54.094
It's them. Stop right there!
Put your hands in the air!

09:54.136 --> 09:56.263
-Really? Are we doing this?
-He's got a gun, General.

09:56.305 --> 09:59.057
Thank you, General.
General, what should we do?

09:59.099 --> 10:00.600
Drop your weapon,
or I will take you out!

10:00.642 --> 10:03.228
-No one is taking anyone out.
-They're fake.

10:03.270 --> 10:05.188
Yeah, the don't know that.
Why did you put that on?

10:05.230 --> 10:07.816
Because it looks stupid
without the guns, okay?

10:07.858 --> 10:09.401
It looked like
a double fanny pack.

10:09.443 --> 10:11.320
Drop you goddamn weapons!

10:11.361 --> 10:13.864
All three of you turds
stop talking right now.

10:13.905 --> 10:15.490
Sorry, ma'am.
General's orders.

10:15.532 --> 10:16.867
That's right, General.

10:16.908 --> 10:18.994
Out here, we respect
the chain of command.

10:19.036 --> 10:20.620
No one outranks
a general.

10:20.662 --> 10:22.456
Anyone shoots anything,

10:22.497 --> 10:24.416
I'm gonna put all three of you
shitheads in jail, too, okay?

10:24.458 --> 10:25.959
-Nate!
-"Nate"?

10:26.001 --> 10:28.378
What? That's my name.
It's a first-name basis.

10:28.420 --> 10:31.089
Nate, just put your hands
in the air, please!

10:31.131 --> 10:32.424
What would you
like me to do --

10:32.466 --> 10:34.217
hands up or remove
my fake weapons?

10:34.259 --> 10:37.054
He's not complying.
Comply! Comply!

10:37.095 --> 10:38.680
To which order?

10:38.722 --> 10:41.058
He's not complying to my order
to comply! General!

10:41.099 --> 10:44.102
Holy shit!
Guys, we're a family, all right.

10:44.144 --> 10:46.229
Nothing's gonna happen.
Don't be stupid.

10:46.271 --> 10:49.441
First you killed General Sleepy,
now you're calling us stupid?

10:49.483 --> 10:51.651
Oh, you are gonna
be in for payback!

10:51.693 --> 10:55.906
I didn't kill him.
He had terminal...something.

10:55.947 --> 10:58.533
He would have told me if he
could remember what it was.

10:58.575 --> 11:00.285
-Oh, God.
-He was old.

11:00.327 --> 11:02.829
I thought he was sleeping in
the plane and then he was dead.

11:02.871 --> 11:05.624
He was dead.
It was a moment for me.

11:05.665 --> 11:08.043
I -- I gave him a eulogy.
I tried to honor him.

11:08.085 --> 11:10.337
We both -- both of us did.
We both wanted that.

11:10.379 --> 11:12.672
And we were gonna burn him,
and then the rain came.

11:12.714 --> 11:14.174
The Alaskan weather.
Edie.

11:14.216 --> 11:16.259
-"Edie"?
-That's her name, okay?

11:16.301 --> 11:17.844
Edie, come on,
you remember Wasilla?

11:17.886 --> 11:19.388
Yes, yes, the thing
with the guy.

11:19.429 --> 11:20.764
Yes. Same thing.

11:20.806 --> 11:22.682
The situation just
got out of control.

11:22.724 --> 11:24.518
It happens, I understand.

11:24.559 --> 11:26.144
Anyway, long story short,

11:26.186 --> 11:28.397
kids got high and kicked him
off a mountain.

11:28.438 --> 11:29.981
I say we take those kids out!

11:30.023 --> 11:33.110
Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Goddamn it, General!

11:33.151 --> 11:34.528
Children are our future.

11:34.569 --> 11:37.489
Guys...
Guys, listen to me. Please.

11:37.531 --> 11:40.242
Everything is gonna be okay.
I promise.

11:40.283 --> 11:42.953
You just have to stop running.

11:46.373 --> 11:47.749
Okay?

11:47.791 --> 11:56.133
♪♪

11:56.174 --> 11:57.801
Reach for the sky.

11:57.843 --> 11:59.302
What the f--
Oh, shit!

11:59.344 --> 12:00.929
Oh, Jesus Christ.
Oh, God!

12:00.971 --> 12:08.437
♪♪

12:08.478 --> 12:11.189
This town ain't big enough
for the two of us.

12:11.231 --> 12:14.401
-What?
-Go ahead...make my day.

12:14.443 --> 12:16.445
No, no, Tanaka-san!
Tanaka-san!

12:16.486 --> 12:18.613
Bad idea! Bad idea!

12:18.655 --> 12:20.407
Edie, Edie!
It's all fake.

12:20.449 --> 12:23.076
Some weird Japanese
cosplay bullshit.

12:23.118 --> 12:25.162
-Wait, what?
-You told me you liked it.

12:25.203 --> 12:27.581
I do. I do. You've done
a magnificent job.

12:27.622 --> 12:29.249
You really have.
Why now?

12:29.291 --> 12:30.709
She really has.

12:30.750 --> 12:32.294
Trust me, we went through
this today already.

12:32.335 --> 12:35.005
It is all fake. They just
love American history.

12:35.046 --> 12:36.756
You think "Fat Man"
and "Little Boy"

12:36.798 --> 12:39.217
would cure them of their love
for cowboys and Sha Na Na.

12:39.259 --> 12:41.219
We got bogeys at all
the o'clocks, General.

12:41.261 --> 12:42.637
I say we light them up!

12:42.679 --> 12:44.973
No, just stop!
Don't do anything!

12:45.015 --> 12:47.434
This is your final warning!
That's a good idea.

12:47.476 --> 12:49.728
General Carol,
send them a warning!

12:51.563 --> 12:54.065
Oh, shit.
What? No!

12:55.567 --> 12:57.277
Go!

12:57.319 --> 13:01.364
♪♪

13:07.370 --> 13:08.747
-[ Laughs ]
-Whoo!

13:08.788 --> 13:10.332
-Yeah! Oh!
-Whoo!

13:10.373 --> 13:15.253
Get on the ground!
Get on the goddamn ground!

13:22.511 --> 13:26.598
I've got the Randalls
and...so much more.

13:26.640 --> 13:31.645
Mm-hmm. Yes, thank you, sir.
It's good to be back.

13:31.686 --> 13:34.940
All right. You did good,
little girl.

13:34.981 --> 13:37.025
Oh!

13:37.067 --> 13:39.986
Put your hands
on top of your head.

13:40.028 --> 13:42.030
Do what she says.

13:42.072 --> 13:44.866
Ow! Oh, oh, shit!

13:44.908 --> 13:46.201
What, what?

13:46.243 --> 13:47.577
I think I dislocated
my shoulder.

13:47.619 --> 13:49.913
Oh, my God.
After all we've been through,

13:49.955 --> 13:51.331
that's the thing
that breaks you?

13:51.373 --> 13:53.500
I haven't done yoga
in a year!

13:55.168 --> 13:57.921
Ow! Oh, God, it hurts!

13:57.963 --> 14:07.889
♪♪

14:07.931 --> 14:17.899
♪♪

14:17.941 --> 14:27.867
♪♪

14:27.909 --> 14:37.836
♪♪

14:37.877 --> 14:47.804
♪♪

14:47.846 --> 14:57.814
♪♪

14:57.856 --> 15:07.782
♪♪

15:07.824 --> 15:10.118
So you wasted how many years
of your life on the run?

15:10.160 --> 15:11.745
About two.

15:11.786 --> 15:13.622
But the important thing
is that we're free.

15:13.663 --> 15:15.832
And alive and...
we're still a family.

15:15.874 --> 15:17.334
Yeah, speaking of which,
where the hell is your sister?

15:17.375 --> 15:18.877
-She's in the bathroom.
-Well, go get her.

15:18.918 --> 15:20.170
We're gonna go.

15:20.211 --> 15:21.504
-Okay.
-Yeah.

15:21.546 --> 15:23.590
If you release them,
I will never find J.R.

15:23.632 --> 15:27.218
They are my hostages --
witnesses! Shit!

15:27.260 --> 15:29.262
Lady, lady, listen to me.

15:29.304 --> 15:31.681
What is your obsession
with my father?

15:31.723 --> 15:34.517
So he owes a few back tariffs?
Okay, he's a multimillionaire.

15:34.559 --> 15:36.186
He can come in here, and he can
write a check tomorrow.

15:36.227 --> 15:37.812
Then why doesn't he?!

15:37.854 --> 15:39.773
I feel like I've been
chasing him my entire life.

15:39.814 --> 15:41.566
Well, you're never
gonna find him.

15:41.608 --> 15:44.569
He's a ghost.
Disappearing is what he does.

15:44.611 --> 15:47.447
Oh, it's just so frustrating!
Yeah, tell me about it.

15:47.489 --> 15:48.948
Try having him miss
your teenage years.

15:48.990 --> 15:50.533
-Yeah, I know.
-Uh, no, I don't think you do.

15:50.575 --> 15:52.077
Do you know how many
birthdays he missed?

15:52.118 --> 15:53.328
-All of them.
-Exactly.

15:53.370 --> 15:54.579
-Mine, too.
-No Christmases.

15:54.621 --> 15:55.914
-None.
-No Thanksgivings.

15:55.955 --> 15:57.624
-No Halloweens.
-He was never there.

15:57.666 --> 16:00.251
-Never!
-Ever.

16:00.293 --> 16:02.712
Office Randall,
sign these release forms

16:02.754 --> 16:04.714
and send these people
on their way.

16:06.925 --> 16:08.968
Randall?
Hmm?

16:09.010 --> 16:10.387
Are you shitting me
right now?

16:10.428 --> 16:12.222
What?
Are you shitting me?

16:12.263 --> 16:13.515
Is that what
this is about?

16:13.556 --> 16:15.600
No!
This is about J.R.

16:15.642 --> 16:17.435
[ Voice breaking ] This is about
someone who has never

16:17.477 --> 16:19.187
had to answer
for what they've done.

16:19.229 --> 16:21.398
And he needs to understand
that choices have consequences

16:21.439 --> 16:24.275
and that he broke
the government's heart!

16:24.317 --> 16:25.985
So it is about that.

16:26.027 --> 16:27.529
Yes.
Oh, my God.

16:27.570 --> 16:29.823
Um, can somebody tell me
what's going on?

16:29.864 --> 16:31.449
Are you serious
right now?

16:31.491 --> 16:33.410
I really thought Vanessa
was the stupid sister.

16:33.451 --> 16:35.412
Oh, she is
my stupid sister.

16:35.453 --> 16:37.622
Your stupid sister.

16:37.664 --> 16:40.125
-Yeah, my stupid sister.
-No, no, no.

16:40.166 --> 16:41.918
Honey, youses' stupid sister.

16:41.960 --> 16:43.962
No, listen, hey, Nate does not
consider her a sister

16:44.003 --> 16:45.213
because they had sex once.

16:45.255 --> 16:46.589
-Holy shit!
-She's your sister!

16:46.631 --> 16:48.299
No, I'm your sister!
It's me!

16:50.510 --> 16:55.724
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
I have a sister!

16:55.765 --> 16:57.642
-Oh, my God!
-I'm right here.

16:57.684 --> 16:59.561
Shh.
It's not about you right now.

16:59.602 --> 17:01.896
Oh, shit!

17:01.938 --> 17:03.898
I never thought this story
would have a happy ending.

17:03.940 --> 17:05.191
No, nobody did.

17:05.233 --> 17:06.526
Who's happy
about me being framed?

17:06.568 --> 17:07.986
I went to prison.

17:08.027 --> 17:10.363
You were gone for two years.
I was very happy.

17:10.405 --> 17:12.115
I just can't wait for this
little guy to meet his aunt.

17:12.157 --> 17:14.367
And his cousins
and his father.

17:14.409 --> 17:16.369
Father?
Uncle. I meant uncle.

17:16.411 --> 17:18.288
I don't know why I said father.
I'm so sorry. So weird.

17:18.329 --> 17:20.039
Then why did you say that?
I just -- 'cause I think

17:20.081 --> 17:21.750
'cause we were talking
about our father,

17:21.791 --> 17:23.585
and so I was, like, thinking
father, but then I was like...

17:23.626 --> 17:25.670
-She conflated it.
-It happens. It just came out.

17:25.712 --> 17:27.422
But you pointed at me,
and you said "father."

17:27.464 --> 17:29.340
No, I didn't. I was, like,
pointing just generally, like,

17:29.382 --> 17:31.092
gesticulating like this.

17:31.134 --> 17:33.178
This is so great.
I'm so excited

17:33.219 --> 17:36.306
that we have this, like,
big happy family now.

17:36.347 --> 17:37.724
[ Both laughing ]

17:37.766 --> 17:40.185
-No.
-We don't need it.

17:40.226 --> 17:43.271
Delilah?
Delilah, we're leaving.

17:44.773 --> 17:46.149
Hey.

17:46.191 --> 17:48.067
Get out.

17:48.109 --> 17:50.653
Delilah?

17:52.614 --> 17:55.158
Delilah?

17:58.620 --> 18:00.455
Oh, shit.

18:04.375 --> 18:06.419
5'5", blonde hair, eyes hazel.

18:06.461 --> 18:08.213
Name is Delilah Cherry Parker.

18:08.254 --> 18:11.174
We have a missing girl, 5'5",
blonde hair, hazel eyes.

18:11.216 --> 18:13.927
Name is Delilah Cherry Parker.

18:13.968 --> 18:17.013
Where is my daughter?
Somebody say something.

18:17.055 --> 18:18.556
Somebody please help.

18:18.598 --> 18:19.849
She's nowhere
in the building.

18:19.891 --> 18:21.684
Trust me, Robin,
I promise we'll find her.

18:21.726 --> 18:23.311
What are you talking about?

18:23.353 --> 18:24.979
You spent the past 20 years
not finding Randalls.

18:25.021 --> 18:26.773
Your sister
the runaway type, kid?

18:26.815 --> 18:28.066
Well, I mean,
she rides a snowmobile,

18:28.107 --> 18:29.609
but usually,
she doesn't go anywhere.

18:29.651 --> 18:32.111
Where is she?!
Baby, baby, it's fine, okay?

18:32.153 --> 18:34.614
She did not run away.
She left her stupid alpaca.

18:34.656 --> 18:36.115
She doesn't go anywhere
without this thing.

18:36.157 --> 18:39.536
Mom, Dad, it's me -- Delilah.

18:39.577 --> 18:42.288
So, I guess by now you
figured out that I've run away.

18:42.330 --> 18:44.582
What?
It wasn't an easy
decision to make,

18:44.624 --> 18:47.168
but it was one I made
a long time ago.

18:47.210 --> 18:49.212
I just want you to know
that I love you all,

18:49.254 --> 18:51.047
but I can probably
do better on my own.

18:51.089 --> 18:53.758
I mean, seriously,
how could I do worse?

18:53.800 --> 18:56.302
Please, don't come
looking for me.

18:56.344 --> 18:57.929
I don't want to be found.

18:57.971 --> 18:59.848
And, frankly, I've learned
from the best.

18:59.889 --> 19:01.683
That means you, Mom.

19:01.724 --> 19:04.686
So believe me when I tell you
you'll never find me.

19:07.146 --> 19:10.692
Robin, she's your daughter.
She loves you.

19:10.733 --> 19:12.318
She probably
just got scared

19:12.360 --> 19:14.445
because of the arrest
and the blowing up a building.

19:14.487 --> 19:15.864
But she's a kid.

19:15.905 --> 19:18.616
She doesn't have the tools
to just disappear.

19:18.658 --> 19:20.285
Robin: The first thing
you need to do

19:20.326 --> 19:22.996
is become someone that
no one's looking for.

19:23.037 --> 19:24.455
So that means
finding dead people

19:24.497 --> 19:26.332
who are around
the same age as you.

19:26.374 --> 19:27.625
Fist bump.

19:27.667 --> 19:29.794
Next up, birth certificates.

19:29.836 --> 19:32.046
Which means you find a lonely
desperate county clerk

19:32.088 --> 19:35.341
who will believe
anything you say.

19:35.383 --> 19:38.344
♪ You are my sunshine ♪

19:38.386 --> 19:41.347
♪ My only sunshine ♪

19:41.389 --> 19:44.559
♪ You make me happy
when skies are gray ♪

19:44.601 --> 19:47.478
What's she gonna do?
She doesn't have any money.

19:47.520 --> 19:50.523
♪ You'll never know, dear ♪

19:50.565 --> 19:53.151
♪ How much I love you ♪

19:53.192 --> 19:55.486
I see you managed to spend
the money I sent you back.

19:55.528 --> 19:56.905
What money?

19:56.946 --> 20:00.533
♪ My sunshine away ♪

20:00.575 --> 20:02.827
Where's she gonna go
on foot in Alaska?

20:02.869 --> 20:04.913
Trust me, not far.

20:04.954 --> 20:06.706
-That's the guy you like?
-Mm-hmm.

20:06.748 --> 20:08.875
But mostly I'm just
using him for his car.

20:11.920 --> 20:14.797
♪ I've always loved you ♪

20:14.839 --> 20:16.758
I promise you have
the full cooperation

20:16.799 --> 20:18.259
of the United States
government.

20:18.301 --> 20:21.596
Trust me, Robin.
We'll find her.

20:21.638 --> 20:24.057
No, you won't.

20:24.098 --> 20:27.018
♪ But now you've left me ♪

20:27.060 --> 20:30.396
♪ To love another ♪

20:30.438 --> 20:36.069
♪ You have shattered
all of my dreams ♪

20:36.110 --> 20:38.738
♪ You are my sunshine ♪

20:38.780 --> 20:42.075
♪ My only sunshine ♪

20:42.116 --> 20:44.953
♪ You make me happy ♪

20:44.994 --> 20:48.081
♪ When skies are gray ♪

20:48.122 --> 20:51.084
♪ You'll never know, dear ♪

20:51.125 --> 20:54.379
♪ How much I love you ♪

20:54.420 --> 20:59.300
♪ Please don't take
my sunshine away ♪

21:02.178 --> 21:07.058
♪♪
